## Document Gateway & URL Contract

This project uses a single HTTP “document gateway” (an Nginx container) to expose files stored on the company file server over HTTP. All tools (doc-control pipelines, purchase order system, etc.) must follow this URL contract.

### 1. Storage root

All files are stored under a single root folder called **`cad_iot`**.

- **Production (Raspberry Pi)**
  - Network share: `\\Pss-dc02\cad_iot`
  - Mounted on the Pi at: `/mnt/cad_iot`
  - Docker bind mount:
    - Host: `/mnt/cad_iot`
    - Container: `/data/cad_root`

- **Development (Windows)**
  - Local folder: `C:\Dev\doc-control\cad_iot`
  - Docker bind mount:
    - Host: `C:\Dev\doc-control\cad_iot`
    - Container: `/data/cad_root`

In both cases, the container only ever sees `/data/cad_root`. The host-specific path is provided via the `HOST_DOC_ROOT` environment variable in `.env`.

```env
# .env (Windows dev)
HOST_DOC_ROOT=C:\Dev\doc-control\cad_iot

# .env (Raspberry Pi)
HOST_DOC_ROOT=/mnt/cad_iot
